alfredsnippet.name: Initializes an array containing the numbers in the specified range where `start` and `end` are inclusive with there common difference `step`.
alfredsnippet.snippet:
const initializeArrayWithRange = (end, start = 0, step = 1) =>
  Array.from({ length: Math.ceil((end + 1 - start) / step) }).map((v, i) => i * step + start);
